\n- @dmuthuk\n\n','2020-02-03 00:23:12'),(811,'Extremes market bubbles can be seen in real time based on the distance of price from any reasonable valuations or projections.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:24:28'),(812,'Your trading methodology has to fit your own belief system, personality, and risk tolerance or you will not be able to stick with it during drawdowns in capital.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:22:25'),(813,'When the market is wrong it will eventually show you by price moving back to reality. This is the main driver of downtrends: distribution.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:23:12'),(814,'If you think making money in the market is easy you\'ve already taken the first step towards a big loss.','2020-02-03 00:23:12'),(815,'Many traders think you need to take high risk for high returns.\n\nWrong!\n\nYou should risk small, let your edge play out, add capital, and compound your gains over time — that\'s how you make it BIG.\n','2020-02-03 00:23:12'),(816,'There isn’t always a trend. Sometimes the market just goes sideways.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:24:28'),(817,'A casino doesn\'t make money by predicting. They manage their risk and let their edge play out — and it\'s the same for trading','2020-02-03 00:36:16'),(818,'Don\'t trade when you feel like trading.  Trade because you see a good opportunity that meets your criteria.  You\'re not looking for the best trade you can find right now. You\'re looking for the right trade. Period','2020-02-03 00:24:52'),(819,'With new jobs people are okay with low starting pay until they gain experience, but with trading they want to double their money in the first month. That is a perfect mindset for losing your whole account quickly.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:24:52'),(820,'If you put money and bananas in front of a monkey, it would choose bananas because it doesn\'t know that money can buy bananas.\n\nWhen you put happiness and money in front of humans, they choose money because they don\'t know that money can’t buy happiness. \n','2020-02-03 00:24:28'),(821,'A trader has to know:\n\nWhen to let a winner run and when to lock in profits. \n\nWhen to cut your loss and when to give it more room. \n\nWhen to trade and when to just stay in cash. \n\nWhen to be aggressive and when to trade small. \n\nThe solution: A trading system with an edge.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:36:16'),(822,'Money buys the freedom to do whatever you want with your time while debt entraps you to do what you don’t what to do because you have payments to make.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:36:16'),(823,'Keep trading losses small so you’re not afraid of them.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:24:52'),(824,'There are always people who say that the rules have changed. But it only looks that way, if the time horizon is too short','2020-02-03 00:41:44'),(825,'Traders & investors that only learn through trial and error, lose to those that learn from other’s trials and errors','2020-02-03 00:36:16'),(826,'Not being afraid of failure is a huge edge you have in the pursuit of success. \n','2020-02-03 00:41:44'),(827,'Knowledge is power? Certainly not\n\nWe all know how to get in shape, lose weight, be nicer, & be productive\n\nBut look around & you\'ll see that the majority isn\'t really living up to their potential\n\nDOING is power. You don\'t need to know more. You need to do more\n','2020-02-03 00:41:44'),(828,'How to trick luck:\n\nSuppose you want a 6 on the dice. If you roll the dice enough times, eventually you will get a 6.\n\nThis also works in real life\n\nIf you keep investing in opportunities with limited downside and huge upside, you will eventually succeed.\n','2020-02-03 00:41:44'),(829,'In expert tennis, 80% of the points are won, while in amateur tennis, 80% are lost. The same is true for wrestling, chess, and investing: Beginners should focus on avoiding mistakes, experts on making great moves','2020-02-03 00:41:44'),(830,'Profitable trading is all about math:\n\nRisk/reward ratios \nPosition sizing\nBacktesting\nDraw downs \nReturns \nWin%\nLosing streak probabilities\nRisk of ruin\nStop losses\nProfit targets \n\nIt’s all math, don’t let your emotions & ego mess up the math of your trading system.\n\n','2020-02-03 01:36:01'),(831,'The price you’ve got to pay for long term performance is giving up focus on short term performance','2020-02-03 03:42:21'),(832,'You can watch a couple of videos on technical analysis and crack on with it \n\nBut trading with technicals has so many unwritten rules, and it’s the trading part you’re interested in, that’s where the money is.\n\nLine drawing ain’t trading\n','2020-02-03 01:36:01'),(834,'If you get to spend your day doing work you enjoy and your evening being with people you love, you have everything you need','2020-02-03 03:42:21'),(835,'Better to be approximately right than precisely wrong','2020-02-03 01:36:01'),(836,'Everyone wants to buy a pullback until they are looking at one.\n\n','2020-02-03 17:26:01'),(837,'Make small bets for big swings, not big bets for a small swing, and wait for a good risk to reward ratio','2020-02-03 03:42:21'),(839,'It is great to not only diversify your watchlist but also diversify your trading signals and systems to smooth the equity curve through different types of market environments.\n\n','2020-02-03 17:26:01'),(840,'If you have a lot of trading and investing information, but you don\'t have a lot of money. Maybe you have the wrong kind of information.\n\n','2020-02-03 17:26:01'),(841,'A perfectly executed trading plan that has no edge will never lead you to the Emerald City... You\'ll just pave your way to financial ruin by laying a yellow brick road that leads to nowhere financed by your own bankroll until you give up or go broke.\n\n','2020-02-03 17:26:01'),(843,'“Be your own boss as early as possible.” - Bill Gates','2020-02-03 19:28:00'),(844,'Tony Robbins: What made you the wealthiest man in the world?\n\nWarren Buffett: Three things- Living in America for the great opportunities, having good genes so I lived a long time, and compound interest.\n','2020-02