 of a Stock Operator\n\n','2020-02-20 19:28:01'),(1217,'“I don’t care what you have to do—if it means walking everywhere and not eating anything that wasn’t purchased with a coupon, find a way to get your hands on 00,000. After that, you can ease off the gas a little bit.” - Charlie Munger\n\n','2020-02-20 21:31:01'),(1218,'“The desire to be right against the trend has destroyed many accounts. Don’t bring your ego to the game.” - \n@prrobbins\n\n','2020-02-20 21:31:01'),(1219,'“Opportunities are available to all. But only a few have execution capabilities.” - @dmuthuk\n\n','2020-02-20 21:31:01'),(1220,'Don’t let anyone tell you your future, you decide.','2020-02-20 23:22:01'),(1221,'“Don\'t fear failure. Not failure, but low aim, is the crime. In great attempts it is glorious even to fail.” - Bruce Lee\n','2020-02-24 23:56:56'),(1222,'“If you are distressed by anything external, the pain is not due to the thing itself, but to your estimate of it; and this you have the power to revoke at any moment.” - Marcus Aurelius\n','2020-02-24 23:44:43'),(1223,'50% of Finance Twitter is people that don’t trade or invest telling the people that do that they’re not doing it right.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:56:56'),(1224,'While fundamentals can be used to build a watchlist of stocks only technicals should be used to trade them.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:50:37'),(1225,'How To Improve Your Trading Performance-8 Steps\n\n1. Have a viable trading strategy\n2. Forget monetary goals; set process goals\n3. Manage your risk\n4. Be less in your head\n5. Trust your approach\n6. Tune out the noise\n7. Keep taking your chances\n8. Keep a journal\n- @TradingComposur\n\n','2020-02-25 00:03:27'),(1226,'It can be very tempting to sell a bull market short. That rarely works because you’re trying to go against the path of least resistance.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:50:37'),(1227,'People always looking for an argument are trying to convince their self and overcome their own doubts.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:10:32'),(1228,'