be not the way you intended, but you will get there. \n\n- @Gymshark \n','2020-02-08 06:13:04'),(1243,'Politicians create more problems than they solve.\n\n','2020-02-08 06:13:04'),(1244,'“I\'m unable to understand people posting  monthly and even daily returns. The minimum period should be one year. Meaningful is five and ten year returns.” - @dmuthuk\n\n','2020-02-08 06:16:32'),(1245,'The biggest part of good trading psychology is developing faith in yourself and your system over time.\n\n','2020-02-08 06:16:32'),(1246,'You have to accept losses and drawdowns as part of the process.\n\n','2020-02-08 06:16:32'),(1247,'Don’t let up days make you greedy or down days make you fearful, stick to your trading system.\n\n','2020-02-08 18:36:52'),(1249,'“The best way to teach your kids about taxes is by eating 30% of their ice cream.”  – Bill Murray\n\n','2020-02-09 19:28:01'),(1251,'If you do these for 30 days you will be unrecognizable:\n\n1. Sleep 8+ hours\n2. Drink 2 liters minimum of water a day\n3. Get sun daily\n4. No sugar\n5. Read for 30 minutes a day\n6. Workout 3x week\n7. Eat fruit + veggies daily\n8. Meditate for 10 minutes daily\n\n- @anandchokshi19\n\n','2020-02-09 19:28:01'),(1253,'You can fuck your whole life up hanging out with people who have no goals or ambitions. \n\n#SundayMotivation\n\n','2020-02-09 19:28:01'),(1254,'Weak goals are same as no goals\n\n','2020-02-09 19:28:01'),(1255,'What are the seven books you would recommend to other traders?\n\nHere\'s my list:\n\n1. Trend Following\n2. Market Wizards\n3. The Man Who Solved the Market\n4. Trade Like A Casino\n5. Trade Your Way to Financial Freedom\n6. How To Make Money in Stocks\n7. Reminiscences of a Stock Operator\n\n','2020-02-09 21:31:00'),(1256,'“Nothing kills ambition like a comfortable monthly paycheck. Why? Because the survival instinct is lost.” - @LifeMathMoney\n\n','2020-02-09 23:22:00'),(1257,'There are 5 ways to accumulate a billion dollars in America: \n\n1) Build a company so good it dominates its industry\n2) Be a trader or investor that manages billions of dollars\n3) Marry a multi-billionaire \n4) Invest big in the best company\n5) Inheritance\n\nSocialists hate them all\n\n','2020-02-09 21:31:00'),(1258,'The goal of trailing stops, like stop losses, is to put the trailing stop loss at a level that shouldn’t be reached if the trend is going to continue.\n\n','2020-02-10 08:56:02'),(1259,'Trades must be asymmetric; the downside risk is carefully planned and managed, but the upside profits are open-ended. This is a critical part of trading success.\n\n','2020-02-10 08:56:02'),(1260,'Large losses are the primary cause of unprofitable trading across all time frames and methods.\n\n','2020-02-10 08:56:02'),(1261,'Choose non-emotional responses to your trading results without being ego driven and see the difference it makes in your profits and losses.\n\n','2020-02-11 06:41:25'),(1262,'“The elements of good trading are: \n\n1. Cutting losses. \n2. Cutting losses. \n3. Cutting losses. \n\nIf you can follow these three rules, you may have a chance.”\n\n- Ed Seykota\n\n','2020-02-21 17:26:00'),(1264,'The value of someone\'s opinion on the markets is worth /bin/bash.\n\nThe value of creating your own trading system with an edge? Priceless.\n\n','2020-02-21 17:26:00'),(1265,'“Life is 10% what happens to you and 90% how you react to it.” - Charles R. Swindoll\n','2020-02-21 21:31:01'),(1266,'Contrary to popular belief, a winning trading strategy isn\'t that hard to come by. \n\nIt\'s behavioral consistency that makes the magic (consistent profitability) happen. \n\nAnd this is the toughest part.\n\n','2020-02-21 21:31:01'),(1267,'Bad losers:\n• Complain\n• Play the blame game\n• Revenge trade\n• Can\'t deal with their own discomforts\n\nGood losers:\n• Accept losses with grace\n• take responsibility\n• Investigate the cause\n• Open to lessons\n\n','2020-02-21 21:31:01'),(1268,'Don\'t let losses trigger your doubts and insecurities.\n\nIt\'s not about you. It\'s just data.\n\nTake note, then move on to the next trade.\n\n','2020-02-21 23:22:01'),(1269,'The market is like a book. Everyone tends to interpret the story a little bit differently.\n\n','2020-02-21 23:22:01'),(1270,'Don\'t become too attached to short term outcomes. Have a strategy with a positive expectancy and play the numbers game.\n\n','2020-02-21 23:22:01'),(1271,'If you like to be right, and actively seek it, you are playing a game of chasing emotional highs; consequently, be prepared for the emotional lows.\n\nIf you don\'t seek to be right and can only focus on placing good trades, right or wrong, your emotions won\'t swing to extremes.\n\n','2020-02-21 23:22:01'),(1272,'Consistency is the direct result of market proficiency, patient effort, and self-control.\n\n','2020-02-22 05:07:15'),(1273,'If you can\'t break the habit of being obsessed over the market and your positions, trading will wear you down faster than anything you\'ve ever experienced.\n\nCultivate a sense of detachment towards the outcome.\n\nIf you want to do well in this field long term, this is the only way.\n\n','2020-02-22 05:16:20'),(1274,'Learning to trade is akin to learning to play an instrument.\n\nMany will learn to play it reasonably well, but few will go the extra mile to become virtuosos.\n\n','2020-02-22 05:16:20'),(1275,'“There seems to be some perverse human characteristic that likes to make easy things difficult.”\n\n― Warren Buffett\n\n','2020-02-22 05:19:43'),(1276,'Learn to manage your open trades without clinging to the outcome; without fear or favor.\n\n','2020-02-22 05:07:15'),(1277,'No amount of guilt can change the past.\n\nNo amount of anxiety can make the future certain.\n\nThe present is all that you have.\n\n- @dmuthuk \n','2020-02-22 07:52:57'),(1278,'Ideas are cheap, consistent execution is the real cost.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:55:37'),(1279,'Risks is the potential cost, reward is the potential reward, time is the currency that determines the size.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:52:57'),(1280,'Shorting the stock market is the path of most resistance.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:52:57'),(1281,'The more you force your eyes to find trades, the less effective you become as a trader.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:52:57'),(1282,'“Ego says, “Once everything falls into place, I\'ll feel peace.”\n\nSpirit says, “Find your peace, and then everything will fall into place.”','2020-02-22 07:52:57'),(1283,'Whenever you catch yourself following some line of thinking that doesn\'t promote happiness and serve your greater goal, gently bring your attention back to the present.\n\nBreak the momentum before those thoughts spill over into the outside.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:55:37'),(1284,'With repeated exposure, you\'ll come to see that your top and bottom calls are right a fair number of times, and they\'re wrong as often.\n\nYou\'ll let go of wanting to predict those turning points and, gradually, you\'ll focus more on placing asymmetric risk-reward trades.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:59:10'),(1285,'In life,\n\nGood things happen; bad things also happen.\n\nIf you fear bad things and refuse to leave your house, you\'re not maximizing your life.\n\nFor good things to happen, you have to risk going through the bad ―good and bad are intertwined.\n\nIt is with trading as it is with life.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:55:37'),(1286,'You could make trading a whole lot easier if you could just adopt a \'set and forget\' approach, instead of your default \'set, watch, and obsess\' approach.\n\n','2020-02-22 07:55:37'),(1287,'When you decide to “Go big or go home” you usually end up back at your house with no money.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:08:05'),(1288,'Many troubles can be avoided just by checking the market less often and having contingent orders in place.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:13:34'),(1289,'In trading you rarely get rich trading a small account, more often small accounts go to zero.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:08:05'),(1290,'If you want to make more money you have to expose yourself to more risk. If you want less risk then trade and invest less.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:08:05'),(1291,'A profitable trading system just needs big wins & small losses. Winning percentage is not the most important factor.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:08:05'),(1292,'“By breaking down our sense of self-importance, all we lose is a parasite that has long infected our minds. What we gain in return is freedom, openness of mind, spontaneity, simplicity, altruism: all qualities inherent in happiness.” \n','2020-02-24 19:13:34'),(1293,'Don\'t think that market success has to come to you fast. Trade small, stay in the game, persist, and, eventually,  you\'ll reach a satisfying level of proficiency. \n\nNot overnight but over time.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:13:34'),(1294,'Before you trade, consider the hidden costs of not following your plan:\n\n• Loss of time\n• Financial loss\n• Frustration, dissatisfaction, discontentment, hopelessness...\n• More trading errors\n\n','2020-02-24 19:21:50'),(1295,'In the long term the risk/reward ratio always favors the bulls in the stock market.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:13:34'),(1296,'“Your odds of success increase dramatically when you replace greed and impatience with study and discipline.” - @prrobbins\n\n','2020-02-24 19:21:50'),(1297,'“If you have trouble imagining a 20% loss in the stock market, you shouldn’t be in stocks.” \n\n– John Bogle\n\n','2020-02-24 19:21:50'),(1298,'Employees make their bosses rich.\n\nDebtors make banks rich.\n\nConsumers make businesses rich.\n\nRenters make their landlords rich. \n\nBonuses make executives rich.\n\nCorruption makes politicians rich.\n\nStock options make start up employees rich. \n\nInvestors make themselves rich.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:21:50'),(1299,'If your risk exposure is too big, fear will override any rational thinking.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:21:50'),(1300,'Living is risking.\n\nEvery advance in human civilization was made possible because someone took risks and challenged the status quo, beginning with the caveman’s invention of tools to the moon landing and gene therapy.\n\nBy all means, do what you are designed to do: Take risks.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:26:17'),(1301,'Casinos don\'t gamble; they rely on the gambling behaviors of others and let the probabilities work for them over many bets.\n\nTraders and investors need to think and act like casinos.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:13:34'),(1302,'Step 1: Write down your top 25 goals.\n\nStep 2: Draw a circle around your top 5 goals.\n\nStep 3: Focus on Your Top 5 Goals and Say No to the Rest\n\n- Warren Buffett \n','2020-02-24 19:26:17'),(1303,'“A losing trader can do little to transform himself into a winning trader. A losing trader is not going to want to transform himself. That\'s the kind of thing winning traders do.” - Ed Seykota\n\n','2020-02-24 19:38:00'),(1304,'If you have trades on and are not a day trader, don\'t sit there and watch the price all day long; you can\'t do anything but wait anyway, so don\'t waste your life staring at a bunch of numbers you can\'t control.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:26:17'),(1305,'Inexperienced traders react emotionally and only value short term outcomes as indicator of success or failure.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:26:17'),(1306,'There is only one way to make it: drop the get-rich-quick mentality, have a strategy, follow it through good and bad, and let the market (and time) reward you.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:26:17'),(1307,'It is in learning to handle difficult and unpleasant emotions that you will become a great trader.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:28:01'),(1308,'The longer I trade the more I am convinced that position sizing and risk exposure will determine your trading success in the long term.\n\n','2020-02-24 19:28:01'),(1309,'Fidelity’s Millionaire Outlook Survey showed 86% of millionaires said they made their own wealth, they didn’t inherit it.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:39:49'),(1310,'When profits don\'t make you as ecstatic, losses won\'t make you as miserable.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:39:49'),(1311,'Everyone –even some of the smartest people alive– are wrong about some of the things they believe to be true.\n\nBeing wrong is not a problem, but not willing to change your mind in the face of evidence is.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:41:14'),(1312,'As your trade is unfolding, pay attention to the thoughts in your mind. \n\nIf there is angst, observe it. If there is desire, observe it. But don\'t add to them.\n\nJust watch and feel whatever comes up.\n\nThis is what mindfulness is and trading can be a wonderful time to practice it.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:44:43'),(1313,'Don\'t bring emotional struggle into trading. Effortlessness is the key to success.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:41:14'),(1314,'Your biggest risk is not a drop in prices. In fact, this can turn out to be an amazing opportunity. Your biggest risk is if a drop in prices has the potential to cause some irreversible damage to your account.\n\n','2020-02-24 23:41:14'),(1316,'I would suggest that you trade only to make money, not for entertainment or to prove something to yourself. Profitable trading is often boring. If you already know what you’re going to do before you trade, it takes a lot of the excitement out of it.\n\n','2020-02-02 23:59:20'),(1317,'Before you place the trade, you need to have an exit strategy of how, when, and why you will take profits and what your stop loss will be. You have to plan to sell your stock at a specific percentage loss, price support breach, or trend change.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:01:21'),(1318,'You need to focus on a sound strategy, system, and trading plan and not profits. Good trading will create your profits, but focusing on your profits will usually lead to bad trading.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:01:21'),(1319,'All your trades should end in one of four ways: a small win, a big win, a small loss, or break even. You should never experience a big loss. If you can get rid of big losses, you have a great chance of being profitable for years to come.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:02:53'),(1321,'Cutting winners short at the beginning of a trend and letting a loser run on the wrong side of a trend, are the two biggest causes of unprofitability.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:01:21'),(1322,'It\'s not so much that consistently profitable traders have an uncanny ability to predict price movement, rather it\'s the fact that they deal with uncertainty in a methodical and consistent way. \n\nTherein lies their strength.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:01:50'),(1323,'You are the captain of this ship. \n\nOnly your own diligence and commitment can bring you the results you desire. \n\nNo one else can do this for you.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:10:47'),(1324,'The hardest thing to learn about trading is the idea that you can be wrong; that it\'s perfectly okay; that a controlled loss is actually a good thing.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:12:24'),(1325,'Based on your analysis, you can approach different trade ideas with different degrees of conviction, but never should you approach them with total certainty in mind.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:12:24'),(1326,'Great traders are profitable because they have become masters at managing uncertainty. They don’t win because they can see the future, they win because they are certain of what they will do, in the present moment, when faced with uncertainty.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:12:24'),(1327,'A trader has to focus on what’s happening, not what they want to happen or hope will happen next. The past is over and the future doesn’t exist yet. All we can do is focus on the present moment.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:12:24'),(1329,'To be successful, you must learn to take your initial stop loss. Following this important rule will give you faith in your abilities. You will prove to yourself that you will always stop a small loss from becoming a big loss.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:12:24'),(1330,'Always focus first on what you can lose, rather than what you could gain.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:19:25'),(1331,'The 1% rule means that you never lose more than 1% of your total trading capital, by implementing proper stop loss and correct position sizing on each trade.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:14:03'),(1332,'To be successful, new traders must realize that trading is about probabilities, trends, and risk management, not prognostication.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:14:03'),(1333,'Growing capital is a result of being in losing trades for the shortest amount of time, while staying in winning trades for as long as possible.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:14:03'),(1334,'Luck is only a tool of short term success, long term success takes a lot of work.\n\n','2020-02-03 00:24:28'),(1335,'The only thing that is easy about trading is turning 0,000 into ,000.\n\n','2020-02-03 21:31:00'),(1336,'“A stone is broken by the last stroke of hammer. That doesn\'t mean that the first stroke is useless. Success is the result of continuous efforts.” - Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam \n','2020-02-03 23:22:00'),(1337,'“If you\'ve got a good income and no desire to impress your neighbours, you\'ll get rich pretty fast.” - @dmuthuk\n\n','2020-02-03 23:22:00'),(1338,'Every trade you do, you should do it with the intimate goal of strengthening your equanimity. Winning trades or losing trades shouldn\'t get to you.\n\n','2020-02-03 23:22:00'),(1339,'Technical analysis is certainly useful, but it\'s definitely not a crystal ball. \n\nAt all times, manage your risk and expectations wisely.\n\n','2020-02-03 23:22:00'),(1340,'Never be overconfident over a trade; instead, have confidence in your strategy and process.\n\n','2020-02-03 23:22:00'),(1341,'There is no trading system of trader that wins all the time every day, week, or month. Markets are always changing and only liars say they catch every new twist and turn.\n\n','2020-02-04 01:36:01'),(1342,'Position sizing determines how big your wins AND losses are.\n\n','2020-02-04 01:36:01'),(1343,'When a trade is going against you, avoid thinking those things that tend to lock you in ego protection mode. When that happens, the craving to be right gets to the forefront of one\'s mind, and reason and trading plan get thrown out of the window.\n\n','2020-02-04 01:36:01'),(1344,'Traders who make money:\n\n1. Manage risk\n2. Are patient\n3. Have a plan\n4. Trust their strategy\n5. Understand the market they\'re trading\n6. Manage their mindset\n7. Think in probabilities\n8. Focus on trading well ―money comes as a result\n\n','2020-02-04 01:36:01'),(1345,'Your employer isn’t your family and there is little loyalty anymore. Recognize the relationship for what it is, a market exchange of your time for money. Believing it is more exposes yourself to a level of emotional abuse. Your paycheck is never guaranteed long term.','2020-02-04 01:36:01'),(1346,'Right + early = wrong\n\nRight + lack of execution = wrong\n\nIn these scenarios, being right only helps egos for many people\n\nEgos don’t pay bills.  Egos don’t change lives.\n\nBy @CrmTrades\n\n','2020-02-04 06:33:21'),(1347,'“Why focus on the process when the world is outcome driven? Don’t results matter?\n\nYes, results do matter. But if you optimize for the outcome, you win one time.\n\nIf you optimize for a process that leads to great outcomes, you can win again and again.”\n\n- @LindaRaschke\n\n','2020-02-04 06:42:12'),(1348,'If you don\'t learn money management, you may get rich someday, but you\'ll be poor again soon after that.\n\n','2020-02-04 06:33:21'),(1350,'“The past repeats as long as behavior repeats.” - @dmuthuk \n','2020-02-04 17:26:01'),(1351,'The more conviction you have in a trade the harder it is to stop a loss or lock in  a profit while it is still there.\n\n','2020-02-04 21:31:00'),(1353,'Right + early = wrong\n\nRight + lack of execution = wrong\n\nIn these scenarios, being right only helps egos for many people\n\nEgos don’t pay bills.  Egos don’t change lives.\n\nBy @CrmTrades','2020-02-04 21:31:00'),(1357,'Don\'t get emotionally invested.\n\nThis is one of the worst attitudes you can bring into trading.','2020-02-04 21:31:00'),(1358,'Losses reflect an important reality of life: good times and bad times are transient.','2020-02-04 23:22:01'),(1359,'Technical analysis is certainly useful, but it\'s definitely not a crystal ball. \n\nAt all times, manage your risk and expectations wisely.','2020-02-05 21:31:00'),(1360,'Never be overconfident over a trade; instead, have confidence in your strategy and process.','2020-02-05 19:28:01'),(1361,'When we talk about trading \'skills\', what we\'re really talking about is the ability to manage our biases, make difficult decisions, and manage our mindset trade after trade.','2020-02-06 19:26:24'),(1362,'You can learn from watching other people trade but you can only trade a system that fits your own return goals and risk tolerance.','2020-02-06 19:26:24'),(1363,'rThe only place people should be looking for trades is on their own watch list and inside their own system.','2020-02-06 19:26:24'),(1364,'People get paid for different things:\n\nCapital gains\nDividends\nBond yield\nStock options\nYour time\nYour sales commissions\nYour knowledge\nYour labor\nRoyalties\nBusiness income\nRent on real estate\nAdvertising\nSpokesperson\nLicensing\nPro sports\n\nWhat’s your favorite cash flow source?','2020-02-06 19:26:24'),(1365,'If you can find something you love to do for a living that can solve 80% of your problems in life.','2020-02-06 19:26:24'),(1367,'Your thoughts and beliefs create your destiny, be careful what you let in your mind because it can become your reality.','2020-02-06 19:28:00'),(1368,'Money is always either growing in stocks and bonds or dying through inflation. Money never quits moving.','2020-02-06 19:28:00'),(1369,'The keys to building wealth in this field: \n\n• Understand the psychology of others\n• Master your own','2020-02-06 19:28:00'),(1370,'If you have a lot of expectations for your trade, take a moment to relax your body and clear your mind, and then see if you can approach it with acceptance.','2020-02-06 23:22:00'),(1371,'Trading, done the right way, makes you self-sufficient. \n\nBut, the trick about self-sufficiency is that it heavily relies on discipline.\n\nSo, can you embody that discipline day-in and day-out?','2020-02-08 22:47:46'),(1372,'“The money that you make is a function of both the Win-rate  and the Risk-Reward ratio.”\n\n“But most of us just think about the Win-rate and that is the main problem.”\n\n-Dr David Paul','2020-02-08 22:47:46'),(1373,'Buying the dip or buying a breakout usually works the best when the majority think it’s a bad idea.','2020-02-08 22:47:46'),(1374,'To multiply capital by 10 times: \n\n  8%: 30 years \n10%: 24 years \n12%: 20 years \n15%: 17 years \n18%: 14 years \n20%: 13 years \n26%: 10 years \n\nAround 12% may be achievable in the coming decade.\n\n- @dmuthuk','2020-02-08 23:22:01'),(1375,'“Success is going from failure to failure without losing your enthusiasm.” - Winston Churchill','2020-02-08 22:47:46'),(1377,'From a behavioral standpoint, you were born to be a sheep; to follow the consensus; to fit in. \n\nBut, trading requires you to stand out.','2020-02-08 22:50:08'),(1378,'A fair number of times, the market will hit your stop-loss and immediately turn around.\n\nA fair number of times, the market will hit your stop-loss and steam further in that same direction.\n\nAlways honor your stop-loss. Don\'t pretend you have a crystal ball.','2020-02-08 22:50:08'),(1379,'Don\'t just look at information that confirms your theories (and there\'s plenty of that); instead, approach trading from a scientific perspective; stay open to information that disproves it. \n\nAssuming that we might actually be wrong is how we protect ourselves.','2020-02-11 06:54:49'),(1380,'“Every day I assume every position I have is wrong.” \n\n― Paul Tudor Jones','2020-02-11 06:55:53'),(1381,'A trading poem by Frank DiCostanzo:\n\nBe wary of events, breaking news, and fear are things that can cost you dear.\n\nPut stops on every trade and know that when markets rain lemons you can\'t always make lemonade.','2020-02-11 06:55:53'),(1382,'“You have power over your mind, not outside events. Realize this, and you will find strength.” - Marcus Aurelius','2020-02-11 06:55:53'),(1383,'Good habits\n\n1. Do homework prior to trades & know the reason why you traded it\n\n2. Develop a Daily/Weekly routine for scanning & executing trades that allows a positive lifestyle outside the screens.\n\n3. Trade within your means (account size), size right sit tight\n\n- @canuck2usa','2020-02-11 19:28:01'),(1384,'If you don’t know what’s your A-Trade, you shouldn’t be trading.','2020-02-11 21:31:01'),(1385,'“Everyone knows. Few execute.” - @dmuthuk','2020-02-22 07:59:10'),(1386,'Time is more important than price. When time is up price will reverse.','2020-02-22 07:59:10'),(1387,'Trading is a marathon, not a sprint. Each trade should be only one of your next 100 with little emotional engagement if you\'re position sizing right.','2020-02-22 07:59:10'),(1388,'You can\'t control the market. You can only:\n\n1. Identify high-probability opportunities\n2. Manage risk           \n3. Train your mind to accept the outcomes of probability-based decisions','2020-02-22 07:59:10'),(1389,'Losses are painful, but they shouldn\'t defeat you.\n\nBecome anti-fragile; develop a tougher skin.','2020-02-24 01:36:01'),(1390,'Narrow your focus. Then narrow it some more. Find the one trade, the one method, the one situation that makes clear sense to you and drill down on it.  Commit to it fully and block everything else out until it pays you. Own that one thing.  Now you have edge.','2020-02-24 01:36:01'),(1392,'You become what you devote your time and attention to.','2020-02-25 00:11:58'),(1394,'If you do these for 30 days you will be unrecognizable :\n\n1. Sleep 8+ hours\n2. Drink 2 liters of water a day\n3. Get sun daily\n4. No refined sugar\n5. Read for 30 minutes a day\n6. Workout 3 times a week\n7. Eat fruit/vegetables daily\n8. Meditate for 15 mins daily\n\n- @anandchokshi19','2020-02-25 00:15:45'),(1395,'Only about 10% of traders & investors have clear, specific, written trading systems & plans that they follow each day. The other 90% have hopes, dreams, wishes, & fantasies, but not quantified trading systems. And the great tragedy is that they don’t know their results are doomed','2020-02-25 00:11:58'),(1397,'Your #1 goal should be happiness whatever that means for you.','2020-02-25 00:11:58'),(1399,'“Debt doesn’t cost only interest. It costs your freedom too.” - @dmuthuk','2020-02-25 00:11:58'),(1403,'Average investors should be able to monitor five to ten companies at a time, but nobody is forcing you to own any of them. If you like seven, buy seven. If you like three, buy three. If you like zero, buy zero.','2020-02-25 00:15:45'),(1406,'The Best Traders\n\nAdmit they can\'t predict the future\n\nConstantly seek to improve systems\n\nListen to new ideas about trading\n\nHave flexible market opinions\n\nAre comfortable taking a stop loss\n\nFollow other great traders\n\nRealize trading is not black & white\n\nFear bias & arrogance','2020-02-25 00:15:45'),(1408,'Trading is not about kicks or get rich quick. Its','2020-02-25 08:12:28'),(1409,'“Every blessing is a curse & every curse is a blessing.” - @garthbrooks','2020-02-25 08:12:28'),(1416,'Ask yourself: What will I make if I\'m right, and what could I lose if I\'m wrong? Look for a risk-reward ratio of three to one or better.','2020-02-25 08:17:26'),(1418,'Don’t make the assumption that simply accumulating trading experience will lead to better performance. If you don’t learn from mistakes and adjust to become better you can just repeat the same mistakes year after year never improving.','2020-02-25 00:15:45'),(1419,'Twenty years of financial discipline would provide forty years of financial independence.\n\nTwenty years of indiscipline would result in forty years of pain and regret.\n\nChoice is yours.\n\n- @dmuthuk','2020-02-11 06:43:28'),(1420,'Most trading problems occur because a trader is unable to sit calmly at their trading desk and do nothing.','2020-02-11 06:44:17'),(1422,'Trading is a psychological game. Most people think they are playing against the market, but the market doesn\'t care. You’re really playing against yourself','2020-02-11 06:44:17'),(1423,'If I had one piece of advice to give to young people, it would be just to don’t get in debt. It’s very tempting to spend more than you earn, it’s very understandable. But it’s not a good idea.','2020-02-11 06:44:17'),(1424,'One of the most difficult skills to develop as a trader is patience. The ability to do nothing when there is nothing to do. Both waiting for a signal or letting a winner run takes a lot of sitting power.','2020-02-11 06:44:17'),(1425,'People greatly underestimate the amount of volatility they can mentally and emotionally handle on the way to achieving returns.','2020-02-24 17:26:01'),(1434,'What leads to a calm and confident state of mind: \n\nHaving a strategy\n\nHaving a plan to implement that strategy\n\nFollowing that plan\n\nTrading the right size ―not too big, not too small\n\nUnderstanding that losing periods never last\n\nSeeing the bigger picture\n\nBy @TradingComposur','2020-02-24 17:26:01'),(1435,'Silence, is the best reply to a fool.','2020-02-24 17:26:01'),(1436,'The market can go down three times as fast as it goes up.','2020-02-24 17:26:01'),(1438,'“The best way to predict your future is to create it.” - Abraham Lincoln','2020-02-24 17:26:01'),(1443,'Your stop loss and position size determine your risk, your profit target determines your best possible reward. Your risk/reward ratio determines what your win percent needs to be for profitability.','2020-02-24 19:48:45'),(1444,'Money can buy consumer goods, experiences, comfort, convenience, travel, technology, and luxury, but it can also buy the freedom to do what you want with your time.','2020-02-24 21:31:01'),(1445,'Your net worth trend is always a reflection of the balance between earning versus spending, investments versus debt, and creating versus consuming.','2020-02-24 22:28:05'),(1446,'A surprising thing is that income is not the primary determinant of net worth, spending usually is.','2020-02-24 21:31:01'),(1447,'Assets are things you own that pay you, liabilities are things that own you that you have to pay the bank to keep.','2020-02-24 21:31:01'),(1448,'You can work at a job selling your time for money or you can use your money to buy back your time by paying others to do what you don\'t want to do.','2020-02-24 22:28:05'),(1449,'The best pay you can receive from a job is in experience, knowledge, connections, and opportunity.','2020-02-24 21:31:01'),(1450,'“At age 11, in 1942 Warren Buffett had a total savings of 15. If invested in S&P 500, the value now would be 06,811. If invested in gold, the value now would be 200. Gold has delivered only 1% of what index has delivered. Better to own businesses than gold.” - @dmuthuk','2020-02-24 23:44:43'),(1451,'Business owners wake up at 4am\n\nBosses wake up at 5am\n\nMillionaires wake up at 6am\n\nEmployees wake up at 7am\n\nBillionaires wake up whenever they want','2020-02-24 23:50:37'),(1452,'The purpose of a trailing stop is to make winning trades as big as possible.','2020-02-24 23:44:43'),(1453,'Managing volatility and capturing trends are the two primary purposes of a trading system.','2020-02-24 23:49:16'),(1454,'If you continually go big with risk, you will eventually go home with no money. Never take on a risk that will wipe you out the first time you are wrong. No one is right every time.','2020-02-24 23:49:16'),(1455,'There is no free lunch in the markets you must earn every bite.','2020-02-24 23:49:16'),(1456,'Confidence should only come after competence. It is very expensive to go confidently in the wrong direction.','2020-02-24 23:49:16'),(1457,'There have been profitable traders & investors of every type and on every timeframe. Just because you can’t do it doesn’t mean it can’t work for someone else.','2020-02-24 23:50:37'),(1458,'There are no universal answers to trading and investing questions. Everyone’s answer depends on their own risk tolerance and return goals.','2020-02-24 23:50:37'),(1459,'Everyone has to trade inside the timeframe that they choose. My trades can last for days or weeks so end of day signals is what I backtest for.','2020-02-24 23:49:16'),(1460,'You don’t need to make money today. You don’t need to make money tomorrow.\n\nTrying to force the market to give you money every day is what causes the market to take your money every day.','2020-02-04 06:33:21'),(1461,'Why I became a trader and wanted to work for myself:\n\n- No alarm\n- No commuting\n- No meetings\n- No coworkers\n- No need to ask for time off\n- No suits\n- Setting my own schedule\n- Unlimited earning potential\n\nWhat motivates you the most?\n\nby @Tradeciety','2020-02-04 06:33:21'),(1462,'“Ultimately, there’s one investment that supersedes all others: Invest in yourself. Nobody can take away what you’ve got in yourself, and everybody has potential they haven’t used yet.” - Warren Buffett','2020-02-04 06:33:21'),(1463,'Successful traders focus on their own trading system, not other people.','2020-02-05 19:28:01'),(1464,'3 levels of personal finance\n\nFinancial peace from the worry of how you will pay your monthly bills\n\nFinancial freedom is the ability to earn a living any way you want\n\nFinancial independence is having the net worth of cash flow to pay your monthly bills even when you do nothing','2020-02-05 19:28:01'),(1465,'As a trader, you’ll be wrong a lot―being wrong shouldn’t scare you.','2020-02-07 17:26:01'),(1466,'The current trend is the most important technical indicator.','2020-02-07 17:26:01'),(1467,'You have 2 choices\nA: You can either sit around & keep doing nothing thinking that something is going to miraculously fall in your lap or\nB: You can get up & make a change today. Remember That the best time to plant a tree was 20yrs ago but the next best time is now!\n\n- @cml41987','2020-02-07 17:26:01'),(1468,'“I think investment psychology is by far the more important element, followed by risk control, with the least important consideration being the question of where you buy and sell.” - Tom Basso @basso_tom','2020-02-07 17:26:01'),(1469,'Focusing on the P&L can be such a destructive way to approach trading. My trading journal always surprises me with insights into \'who I am\' and my behavioral patterns. I really think to trade well, you need to have exceptional self-awareness.','2020-02-08 06:01:19'),(1470,'You become what you consume.\n\nThe food you eat will make your body.\nThe information you read will make your mindset.\n\nBe intentional about what you put in yourself.\n\n- @farnamstreet','2020-02-08 06:01:19'),(1471,'Investing should be more like watching paint dry or watching grass grow. \n\nIf you want excitement, take 00 and go to Las Vegas.','2020-02-08 06:01:19'),(1472,'“The secret recipe for success in stock market is simple. 30% in market analysis skills, 30% in risks management, 30% in emotion control, and 10% in luck.” - Benjamin Lee','2020-02-08 06:09:59'),(1473,'Many traders believe that stop losses are the ultimate risk management tool\n\nHowever, if you trade long enough, you will experience a 50% gap-down or more, in which case a stop loss does nothing\n\nTherefore, the only true risk management tool is position sizing\n\n- @ChartingTrends','2020-02-08 06:01:19'),(1474,'Things schools don\'t teach: \n\nHow to invest\nHow to manage risk\nHow to manage stress \nHow taxes work \nHow money works \nHow to be an entrepreneur  \nHow to think for yourself\nHow to build your net worth\nHow to marry right \n\nInstead kids learn how to give the teacher what they want.','2020-02-08 06:09:59'),(1475,'Buying: 10%\nSelling: 10%\nWaiting: 80%\n\nWealth is primarily created by waiting. In other words, time creates wealth.\n\n- @dmuthuk','2020-02-08 06:01:19'),(1476,'Bulls eat steak,... bears eat ramen..','2020-02-20 05:30:58'),(1477,'“Never underestimate the power of a momentum move. Up or Down. Once the freight train is in motion, it will keep going much further than most have anticipated” - @traderstewie','2020-02-20 05:30:58'),(1478,'That lottery mindset is exactly why people lose so much money in the markets. A system with an edge is what builds and keeps most wealth over the long term, not one pick.','2020-02-20 05:33:08'),(1479,'It\'s okay to be wrong; it\'s unforgivable to stay wrong.','2020-02-20 05:30:58'),(1480,'When you\'re right, have the patience to be right big. When you\'re wrong, have the discipline to be wrong small.','2020-02-20 05:30:58'),(1481,'Good trading is boring; bad trading is exciting and makes the hair on the back of your neck stand up. You can be a bored rich trader or a thrill-seeking gambler. It\'s entirely your choice.','2020-02-20 05:33:08'),(1482,'Most of the time people think these goals are crazy:\n\nPro baseball player\nNFL player\nNBA player\nEntrepreneur \nMillionaire\nRetire early\nTrader\n\nMany think they\'re impossible.\n\nThere are people that are successful in all these with hard work & perseverance','2020-02-20 05:30:58'),(1483,'Work for freedom not for going in debt for things that trap you in a job forever.','2020-02-20 17:26:01'),(1485,'There is an old saying among technicians:\n\n\'The bigger the base, the bigger the move.\'\n\nWhile there are plenty of cases where short-term bases produce excellent results, always be on the lookout for a break out from a very large base formation.','2020-02-20 17:26:01'),(1486,'More data—such as paying attention to the eye colors of the people around when crossing the street—can make you miss the big truck.','2020-02-20 17:26:01'),(1487,'“Other than home loan, if you have any other loan, don’t start investing. Repay the loans first and then invest.” - @dmuthuk','2020-02-20 17:26:01'),(1488,'“Choose a job you love, and you will never have to work a day in your life.” - Unknown','2020-02-20 17:26:01'),(1489,'The first step to success is belief.\n\nThe second step is research.\n\nThe third step is work. \n\nThe fourth step is perseverance.','2020-02-22 05:03:25'),(1490,'Paul Tudor Jones proved it is possible to be a profitable trader\n\nMarty Schwartz proved successful day traders exist\n\nWarren Buffett proved value investors can beat the market\n\nPeter Lynch proved a money manager can beat their index for decades\n\nIt is not easy, but not impossible','2020-02-22 05:03:25'),(1491,'When I move my stop, it\'s like saying,  \'I know I\'m wrong, but feel free to take more of my money, because at this point I\'m not a trader,  I\'m just wishing I was.','2020-02-22 05:07:15'),(1492,'A strong desire for certainty will limit your success in life.','2020-02-22 05:03:25'),(1493,'v','2020-02-22 05:03:25'),(1494,'A stock\'s performance doesn\'t equal the underlying companies performance. A stock can price in the future or discount the present.','2020-02-22 05:07:15'),(1495,'The stock market is always trying to price in new future probabilities each day.','2020-02-22 05:07:15'),(1496,'Having written goals is the first step in any successful journey. You have to know where you’re going.','2020-02-22 05:03:25'),(1497,'Mindfulness will help you stay rational, in control, and focused on the process of trading well.\n\nIt is a skill all traders should strive to develop.','2020-02-24 23:22:01'),(1498,'Different paths to trading decisions:\n\nHope\nFear\nOpinion\nPrediction\nEgo\nSystematic\nIf this/then that process\nAnger\nDesperation \nJust buy & hold\nPerma-bull\nPerma-bear\nStay in cash\n\nWhat do you use the most?','2020-02-24 23:22:01'),(1499,'Money is made and lost only on the exit, while the majority put almost all their efforts on the entry.','2020-02-24 23:22:01'),(1500,'Trading is....\n\nBuying: 10%\nSelling: 10%\nWaiting: 80%','2020-02-24 23:22:01');
